Bobby Watson Masterclass "My favorite Tools & Concepts” LIVE Masterclass + Q&A! DETAILS: http://JazzHeaven.com/live
#bobbywatson #colorofchange #jazzheaven
Bobby covered:
"My favorite Tools & Concepts"
His first live masterclass went so well, he HAD to come back soon!

* Practicing: It's not what you do, it's the way you do it!

* How to have fun slowing things down

* Phrasing made easy

* My System: Less is More!

Masterclass + Q&A + 1-on-1 HOT SEATS where YOU can be live on screen via webcam & get 1-on-1 Feedback from Bobby!

Details: http://JazzHeaven.com/live 

About BOBBY WATSON:

​Veteran Alto Saxophonist Alert!

Bobby was the musical director for Art Blakey's Jazz Messengers for five years and played & recorded with the likes of Wynton Marsalis, Branford Marsalis, Max Roach, Joe Williams, Dianne Reeves, Lou Rawls & Betty Carter.

His renowned band Horizon recorded for the Blue Note and Columbia record labels.

He also composed a song for the soundtrack to the Robert De Niro movie "A Bronx Tale.
A skilled educator, Bobby taught at schools like William Paterson University and Manhattan School of Music and was a distinguished professor & director of jazz studies at the University of Missouri while still managing a worldwide performing schedule.

Details: http://JazzHeaven.com/live
